I have a query (see above) that uses a term aggregation combined with a top-hits aggregation to achieve field collapsing. 
As suggested in the top-hits documentation an additional max-aggregation is used to sort the term buckets by their score.
This is working when the request is submitted using curl but NOT using the java API.

Using curl I can adjust the "size" of the term aggregation from x to x + y and the first x elements are sorted EXACTLY the same, which is needed for paging.
Using the java API the order is 1) different from the curl request and 2) changes when i adjust the size parameter.
In my case, the _score for every bucket is the exact same and using the java API the sorting doesn't seem to be stable.

I have found a workaround for my case using a second sort criteria as a tie breaker: 

```
"order": [
	{
	"top_hit": "desc"
	},
	{
	"_term": "asc"
	}
]
```
